name: Elegant Loft Conversion Ex Marble Workshop
description:
A wrought-iron spiral staircase leads down to the romantic, light-filled space of this welcoming split-level loft with private garden. The original loft interior in industrial style was designed by renowned Milanese architects. Available only for medium long contract.

Huge, well restored, former marble workshop open space of 110 mq + 30 mq garden,
A lot of light. Fully carrefully equipped, industrial atmosphere with raw loft details.
The loft, designed and decorated by Mariaplatz, a group of well-known young Milanese architects, is an open space flat on two floors, quiet and charming.
On the ground floor there is a living room with flat screen TV, a big sofa wich can became two single beds if requiered, kitchen and a bathroom with shower. The open space bedroom on the mezanine overlooks the living room.
Fresh sheets and towels will be provided at your arrival.

SERVICES
- double bed
- big sofa
- vacuum cleaner
- hairdry
neighborhood_overview:
The neighbourhood is cool and full of artist studios, fashion offices: old factories now converted into different kinds of business ranging from photography and fashion firms, to music labels and private flats.
Along the Navigli side you can either walk, run or have fun time among nice shops and cool bars of the area (Navigli-Tortona).
10 mins walking distance from the design area
Perfect Location during the Salone del Mobile and fashion week.

The neighborhood is quiet and very well connected to the center and zona Tortona although Expo 2015 works are blocking part of the town. Navigli, Università Bocconi, Porta Ticinese and Colonne di San Lorenzo are 10-20 minutes walking distance with a large selection of restaurants, bars, historical areas and parcs to enjoy Milan.

- A supermarket, shops, pizzeria, sushi or vegetarian restaurants (good or cheap) along the street.
- Milano's best ice cream only few steps from home
host_about:
I'm young  professional, responsible host who loves travelling and enjoying life! 
Rita

name: Quiet design apartment-Parco Sempione
description:
enjoy a stylish experience in this centrally-located apartment a few step from the center.
The perfect place to relax and enjoy the typical classy neighborhood with restaurants and cafes and boutiques.
Experience an apartment with character and design furnitures.
neighborhood_overview:
Living in the Arco della Pace area means living in a dynamic context, full of restaurants, nightclubs, shops and much more.
The proximity to Parco Sempione makes this area even more interesting, because it is perfect for those who do not want to leave the center but at the same time also for those who are not willing to give up a green area a few steps from the centre.

Very close is Chinatown, a multi-ethnic neighborhood located around the pedestrian street Paolo Sarpi. The streets are decorated with Chinese lanterns, characteristic colors, the scents of oriental spices, posters and ideogram signs. A place that is definitely worth a visit, if you want to immerse yourself at least for a while in an alternative Milan among ravioli, ramen, bubble tea and small shops.
There are many dining options available, from restaurants serving dim sum, to tea houses and stalls offering Asian snacks.
host_about:
Sono una milanese dinamica ed estroversa. Amo la mia città e nel tempo libero mi dedico al nuoto e alla scoperta di posti sempre nuovi.
Le mie mete preferite sono: New York sicuramente al primo posto!! Il sud est asiatico per la spiritualità , la serenità delle persone e i templi, il sud america per la movida e la cucina e ovviamente l'Italia con i suoi infiniti angoli da scoprire.
Leggo soprattutto saggi e testi tematici. Non amo i romanzi in quanto non sono storie vere...
Ascolto tutta la musica tranne heavy metal, hard core, rock pesante..
Sono una buon gustaia.. prediligo secondi e dolci ma non disdegno i primi piatti!!!

description:
Surrounded by the lively atmosphere of Zona Tortona, it offers the perfect combination of comfort and style.
A few steps from the Porta Genova metro, you will find yourself close to the famous Navigli and the relaxing Parco Solari.
Inside, two double bedrooms with large wardrobes, while the bright living room opens onto a balcony, allowing you to enjoy the urban panorama.
The kitchen is fully equipped to prepare delicious dishes.

neighborhood_overview: Zona Tortona is the pulsating neighborhood of Milan, famous for its creative spirit and its lively artistic scene. This trendy area is the ideal place to immerse yourself in contemporary art and design, hosting events and exhibitions throughout the year. With the P. Genova metro station just a stone's throw away, you are connected to the whole city. The picturesque Navigli, with its restaurants and nightlife, are a short drive away, offering an unparalleled dining and entertainment experience. The peaceful Solari Park is perfect for relaxing and regenerating in the midst of greenery. This neighborhood embodies modern Milan, a combination of culture, art and entertainment.

description:
A little house all to yourself! A lovely mini-BILOCALE (Private entrance,kitchen,bedroom and bathroom) ideal for SMART WORKING with FREE WIFI and AIR CONDITIONING.

In a strategic position to experience Milan in all its forms: Business, Art, Culture, Fairs, Sports Events, Fashion and Movida, because you are close to everything, to the CENTER, to the STADIUM, FIERA MILANO CITY, MI.CO, Parco Sempione, RAI, the MALPENSA Shuttle stop, in one of the most known and lively areas of the city, with its restaurants and clubs.
neighborhood_overview:
The Corso Sempione is an elegant and essentially residential street, but the area in which it is located, full of shops of all kinds and full of bars, restaurants and trendy clubs, is also extremely renowned for its nightlife. However, it remains a quiet and normally safe area even at night. The downside could be on some good season nights, the music or the sounds of the "movida". But we are on the seventh floor and there is air conditioning to keep the windows closed, in case you have a particularly light sleep.

The Sempione course ends, or rather begins, with the Arch of Peace, beyond which the famous Sempione Park develops, through which you reach the Sforza Castle and the full center. On good days you can get to the Castle and the Duomo with a pleasant walk through the park.

Despite being a practically central area, it is located to the northwest of the city, on the same part of the Rho Fiera Expo headquarters, easily accessible, without having to cross the ci
host_about: Mi è sempre piaciuto ospitare, conoscere nuova gente e condividere. Fa parte del mio carattere e forse, a quanto si dice, anche del mio essere "Milanese d.o.c." da generazioni!  Farne "una specie di lavoro" è stato un passo naturale. Amo tante cose , la casa e il "sentirsi a casa" che può succedere anche a migliaia di km se stai bene dove sei... Il cibo e il buon vino, e tutte le piccole gioie della vita. I sorrisi...  Elencare le mie passioni quindi sarebbe molto lungo, perchè amo la vita. Solo alcune, quelle più particolari: i cavalli (ho fatto per diversi anni gare di salto ostacoli) e il Tango Argentino.

It is full of restaurants of any culture, traditional and innovative, as well as places where you can enjoy the typical Milanese aperitivo/happy hour.
There are supermarkets open 7 days a week, banks and several stores.
Amongst the main must-see of the area: the suggestive QC Terme di Milano, the Ravizza Park, the Museum and Tower at Fondazione Prada, the late baroque building complex Rotonda della Besana. Bocconi University is at 5 minutes walk.
On Fridays there is a historical food market very nearby where you can enjoy the neighborhood daily lifestyle.
host_about:
Ciao a tutti!
Siciliana di origine, vivo ormai da tempo a Milano insieme a mio marito e i miei figli. 
Da anni ormai abbiamo intrapreso questa nuova avventura come host AirBnB ed è un piacere ricevere ospiti da ogni parte del mondo. Spero che troverete in questo delizioso appartamento la soluzione ideale per i vostri viaggi a Milano!

neighborhood_overview:
Brera is a sophisticated and elegant area in the heart of Milano's city center, walking distance to the Duomo, to the Sforzesco Castle, to La Scala Theatre, and to the Fashion District. Elena

The NoLo district has risen to prominence in the media for its incredible social redevelopment and for the great work of integration and multiculturalism that it enjoys. The neighborhood is a community founded on Inclusion & Diversity, loved and frequented by the LGBTQ+ community that helps and supports each other. Around the neighborhood, green spaces and the wonderful Martesana canal (navigable up to Pavia) offer a mix of nature, craftsmanship, history and great modernity.
The Art Nouveau/Old Milan architecture gives visitors an interesting overview halfway between the past and the metropolis.
host_about: Sono una scrittrice, e sono consulente per le strategie di comunicazione d'impresa. Ho due figli, Nicole di 31 anni che vive a Barcellona, e Jonathan di 23 che vive con me. Ho viaggiato per 7 anni intorno al mondo a bordo di una barca vela quando i miei figli erano piccoli ma poi ho desiderato tornare a Milano, nella mia casetta d'epoca e tra gli amici di sempre. Ho scritto un libro che parla di questo, si intitola Siamo Liberi (Chiarelettere) e mi ha permesso di conoscere tantissime e bellissime persone. Vivo in mezzo ai libri e la mia casa ha più librerie che mobili, li metto a disposizione degli ospiti. Amo la musica e mi trovi molto attiva sui principali social e su Linkedin e sul web in generale. Organizzo percorsi di Resilienza: dalla mia storia ne ho imparata tanta e mi piace condividere questo bel modo di approcciare la vita! Amo le scarpe, faccio collezione di profumi e ho due gatte bellissime. Sono sempre al telefono ma a volte stacco tutto e resto in silenzio per ore. Mi concentro sul bello che c'è intorno a me, e preferisco pensare che il mondo sia pieno di belle persone piuttosto che evidenziare il contrario. Amo il buon cibo, il buon vino, i buoni libri e il buon cinema.

neighborhood_overview: Brera is a sophisticated and elegant area in the heart of Milano's city center, walking distance to the Duomo, to the Sforzesco Castle, to La Scala Theatre, and to the Fashion District. Known as the former Artists area (painters, but also poets and writers used to live and work here), it still maintains its fascinating aura.  It's a very special neighborhood where you can still sense a creative unique atmosphere.  Stroll around the narrow pedestrian streets, set among elegant exclusive buildings, with lots of cafes, restaurants, museums and fashion and design shops. The flat is in a nice street, and right in front of a beautiful ancient church. Shopping, Art, Design and good Food are the main traits of the neighborhood. A beautiful park is very close, just 5 mins away.

neighborhood_overview: The Porta Venezia neighborhood is one of the most characteristic in the city. You can find all kinds of services and shops. Thanks to the numerous restaurants, bars and clubs, the evening lights up with a lively nightlife that makes it safe even if you return late in the evening. The main attractions in the immediate vicinity are: the Natural History Museum, the Planetarium, the neoclassical Villa Reale, home of the GAM, the PAC, and Villa Necchi Campiglio. The city center can be reached on foot in a few minutes with a very pleasant walk along Corso Venezia, where some of the most elegant buildings in Milan overlook. name: TREBBIA5: PORTA ROMANA, BOCCONI-GREAT FOR FAMILIES
description:
Lovely terrace and kids friendly: in the heart of Milan, in Porta Romana area, on the 7th floor of a modern building. The apt is very spacious and comfortable with a charming fireplace in the entrance. You'll find a big sitting room with kitchen, 2 tables, 1 spacious sofa bed, 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom recently renovated, 1 small balcony and a big terrace.
Suitable for families, groups of friends and people travelling for work.
neighborhood_overview:
Art, spas and many restaurants, bars, co-working spaces and clubs liven up the life of Porta Romana. The arch by the same name, in Piazzale Medaglie d'Oro, was one of the six main access gates to Milan, an integral part of the Spanish walls built to strengthen the defense of the city by Governor Ferrante I Gonzaga. Nearby is Casa Sartorio, a building designed by Enrico Provasi in 1910, that calls to mind, on a small scale, the Flatiron Building in New York City. To indulge in a relaxing break, in Porta Romana there is an ancient spa with a view of the Roman aqueduct. It is worth visiting Giardino della Rotonda della Besana, a former cemetery and now a green area with an English-style lawn, and the deconsecrated Church of S. Michele ai Nuovi Sepolcri.

name: Charming Loft in Milan Porta Nuova
description: 250 square meters Loft on 3 levels located in strategic area close to Garibaldi, Brera, Isola
neighborhood_overview:
Porta Nuova is Milan's most modern neighborhood, surrounded by the iconic skyscrapers that have changed the face of the city. Within easy walking distance are the nightlife districts such as Porta Garibaldi/c.so Como and Brera; the fashion district is also within walking distance. There are many restaurants within walking distance from the LOFT. Walking down the street from the LOFT you can reach Eataly, temple of food and wine made in Italy. Just a few steps away is the nightlife of Corso Como and Corso Garibaldi, as well as the pedestrian elevated walkway that connects Milan's new skyscrapers with Porta Garibaldi station and overlooks BAM (Library of Trees), the brand new urban park that surrounds the iconic "Bosco Verticale," judged the most beautiful skyscraper in the world.
Next to the LOFT is a well-equipped supermarket open 24/7.

name: PIAZZA SAN MARCO 1: POP APARTMENT IN BRERA
description:
Nice and comfortable downtown apt located in a building designed by Vico Magistretti, in front of the beautiful San Marco church. Located in Brera: an extremely fascinating area, the most sophisticated neighborhood in town, the former Artists' district, surrounded by elegant shops, lovely restaurants and lively bars. Pedestrian Area nearby. Accademia di Brera, Dome and Castello Sforzesco few steps away. Very lively district.
BE AWARE THAT THE FLAT CON BE NOISY AT NIGHT
neighborhood_overview: Brera is a sophisticated and elegant area in the heart of Milano's city center, walking distance to the Duomo, to the Sforzesco Castle, to La Scala Theatre, and to the Fashion District. Known as the former Artists area (painters, but also poets and writers used to live and work here), it still maintains its fascinating aura. It's a very special neighborhood where you can still sense a creative unique atmosphere. Stroll around the narrow pedestrian streets, set among elegant exclusive buildings, with lots of cafes, restaurants, museums and fashion and design shops. The flat is in a nice street, and right in front of a beautiful ancient church. Shopping, Art, Design and good Food are the main traits of the neighborhood. A beautiful park is very close, just 5 mins away.

name: Charming traditional central apartment
description:
In the heart of Milan, our spacious apartment is located in one of the most beautiful and sparkling areas (Piazza 5 Giornate/Porta Romana), in a charming traditional house.
Within walking distance plenty of shops, restaurants, pizzerias and all amenities facilities, but once back home, you can enjoy the quiet and comfort.
We are in front of the IED (European Institute of Design). Duomo is a 15-minute walk and you can reach all the places of interest easily by public transport.
neighborhood_overview:
We are located a stone's throw from Piazza V Giornate, on a quiet street in front of the IED: nearby you will find a large number of bars and restaurants for all tastes (up to the Knam pastry shop), green areas (the beautiful Rotonda della Besana and Parco Marinai d 'Italia), Corso XXII Marzo with its many shops for shopping and not least Porta Romana and the Terme di Milano.
The Duomo is a 15-minute walk, 5 tram stops, or 10 minutes by bike using the bike sharing services available. You can easily reach all the places of interest in Milan by public transport. You will find all the directions and our suggestions: we are available for advice and for any need.

name: Porta Venezia Vibrant Atmosphere: bright&new flat
description:
Small fully furnished flat in the heart of Porta venezia neighborhood: very central. Lots of shops, nice cafes, trendy restaurants and bars open till late evening. This apartment is in the best location you could ask for, in a very lively area: with a big park across the street & public transportation around the corner. Very easy to reach from the Central station in 8 minutes.
There's no better location to explore the city, all the main attractions are walking distance or very easy to reach!
neighborhood_overview: Porta Venezia is a lively and international neighborhood in a very central area of the city. Full of nice shops, lovely cafes and cool Italian and multiethnic restaurants, it's a very pleasant place to discover; stroll around during the day (do some shopping in the area) or at night (have an "aperitivo" and enjoy the real spirit of Milano).  Reach Piazza San Babila and the Duomo with a pleasant walk (15 min) through a beautiful park, Giardini Pubblici 2 mins walk from home if you like jogging or you have children with you, and along the Fashion District; shop along corso Buenos Aires (1 min walk), the longest commercial shopping street of the city.  Very close to Brera and its sophisticated shops and restaurants, and the newly built area of Piazza Gae Aulenti and Isola districts. SUPERMARKET open 7 days a week 50 m from home Pharmacy in the building Cinema around the corner (movies in English on Tuesdays)

Thisarea offers a delightful mix of history, art, and urban modernity.

name: Corso di Porta Nuova 34: Downtown Jazz Vibes
description: Modern and sophisticated apartment ideal for families and groups of friends who want to explore Milan while feeling at home away from home. Located in the Porta Nuova area, between the elegant Brera/Garibaldi/Moscova districts and the vibrant nightlife of the Gae Aulenti/Isola area: from here you can reach all the main attractions of the city in a 15/20-minute walk. Neighborhood full of bars, restaurants and shops, supermarket 100 meters away.  Green metro Moscova stop, bus and tram nearby
neighborhood_overview:
The Porta Nuova neighborhood is the symbol of contemporary Milan.
Started in 2009, it's one of the biggest urban redevelopment projects in Europe. Through the recomposition of the three neighborhoods Garibaldi, Varesine and Isola, it covers a total of over 340,000 square meters and represents a perfect union between city identity and European vision.
It combines the different areas with a pedestrian system consisting of green areas, squares, bridges and bike paths with elevated walkways. A safe and easy connection between different neighborhoods.

Among the most significant buildings, the complex of towers overlooking Piazza Gae Aulenti with the Unicredit Tower, the Diamond Tower between Viale della Libererazione and Via Galilei, the three towers Aria, Solea and Solaria, the highest residential building in Italy.

name: Sarpi 50: a gem in town with a chandelier
description: Delightful studio, cozy and modern, located inside a courtyard building, typical of old Milan. A single environment with a living area separated from the sleeping area to create an intimate and relaxing atmosphere. Located in the heart of Chinatown, precisely on Via Paolo Sarpi, in the pedestrian area full of shops, boutiques, supermarkets and restaurants. Strategic area to easily reach all the main attractions on foot and well served by public transport.
neighborhood_overview: The Chinatown neighborhood boasts a unique identity and energy: here, Milan meets the East in a perfect exchange of styles and cultures. neighborhood_overview:
In this bohemian chunk of Italy’s financial capital, the modern blocks of the city centre make way for pastel-coloured houses, cobblestone canal pathways and bridges.
Located in the city's south-west corner, the Navigli district remains one of the last true connections the Milanese have with water. The Grand Canal (Naviglio Grande) itself dates back to 1177, making it one of the oldest navigable canals in Europe. Today, it’s packed with bars, cafes, restaurants, art galleries and boutiques; it's a lively meeting spot or a place for a gentle passeggiata stroll by the water.
The Darsena (meaning "dock" or "shipyard") sits at the meeting point of two of Milan’s last canals, Naviglio Grande and Naviglio Pavese. Once one of the busiest ports in Italy until it was decommissioned during the rapid urbanization of the 1960s, this harbour-side area was nothing more than overgrown swamp until it was completely renovated for the Milan Expo. The arch by the same name, in Piazzale Medaglie d'Oro, was one of the six main access gates to Milan, an integral part of the Spanish walls built to strengthen the defense of the city by Governor Ferrante I Gonzaga. Nearby is Casa Sartorio, a building designed by Enrico Provasi in 1910, that calls to mind, on a small scale, the Flatiron Building in New York City. To indulge in a relaxing break, in Porta Romana there is an ancient spa with a view of the Roman aqueduct. It is worth visiting the Giardino della Rotonda della Besana, a former cemetery and now a green area with an English-style lawn, and the deconsecrated Church of S. Michele ai Nuovi Sepolcri.

A few steps away is the New Bocconi University Campus designed in this area in 1941 redesigning the district with its rationalist architecture. The district is very young, frequented by university students, but also full of

neighborhood_overview: A vibrant and historic neighborhood in Milan, known for its eclectic blend of modernity and tradition. Walking distance from Duomo and Navigli, this area is famous for its picturesque canalside scenery and lively atmosphere. Quaint cafes, trendy boutiques, and vintage shops line the streets, creating a unique and charming ambiance. The neighborhood comes to life in the evening when locals and visitors alike gather at the numerous bars and restaurants to enjoy the lively nightlife. Artistic expression thrives in Ticinese, with street art and cultural events adding to its bohemian character. The Basilica di San Lorenzo in Piazza Vetra, an ancient church with a rich history, stands as a testament to the area's cultural heritage. Whether strolling along the canal Navigli, exploring art galleries, or indulging in authentic Italian cuisine, Ticinese offers a captivating and diverse Milanese experience.

description: A little gem in Isola Gae Aulenti area. Enjoy a coffee or a glass of wine on the balcony with an amazing view of Gae Aulenti skyscrapers, and taste Milano Design soul. The flat is set in Isola district, one of the most lively and interesting of the city. Lots of bars, restaurants and shop will offer you the chance to enjoy this area and its very different aspects, that are all mixed together: Isola district is modern, traditional, effervescent, international and much more! A lot to discover....
neighborhood_overview: Isola is certainly the most vibrant, innovative and alternative area of the city. Located in the northern area of Milan, it has been redeveloped and enhanced from its previous state of suburbia. The modern revival integrated well with the old Art Nouveau or rationalist style buildings, the public housing and the street art on the walls and store shutters. A must-see is the ancient Sanctuary of Santa Maria alla Fontana, dating back to 1500, in whose underground area one can find a spring with healing properties and the Fonderia Napoleonica Eugenia where bells were made and bronze casting such as that for the statue of Vittorio Emanuele II in Piazza Duomo was carried out. Now, the building is a historical museum where exhibitions and events take place. In this trendy district you can go shopping in craft stores, thrift stores and boutiques, have an aperitif, have dinner in traditional and ethnic restaurants and end the evening with a jazz concert in one of the many nightclubs.

With a pleasant walk, or if you prefer in 20 minutes by tram, you can visit the most characteristic and historical areas of Milan:

- Duomo di Milano: The majestic Gothic cathedral, symbol of the city, a short tram distance.

- Navigli and Darsena: The evocative canal area, perfect for an evening walk or a romantic dinner in one of the many typical restaurants.

- MUDEC: The Museum of Culture, a short walk away, ideal for those who love contemporary art and culture.

- Castello Sforzesco: An imposing castle that houses museums and exhibitions, rich in history and charm.

- Teatro alla Scala: The temple of world opera, where you can experience exciting evenings of music and show.

- Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II: One of the oldest shopping centers in the world, perfect for luxury shopping.

neighborhood_overview:
The Navigli District is one of the most loved and best-known in Milan, for its beauty and the lively nightlife that characterizes it. It is located south of the city, near monuments to visit such as the Basilica of Sant'Eustorgio or San Lorenzo alle Colonne (another area of the nightlife), and offers the opportunity to walk along the banks of the Naviglio Grande and Naviglio Pavese, stopping for a drink or shopping in the many artisan shops.

The Navigli of Milan were born as artificial navigable canals used for the transport of people and goods and for irrigation: the city in fact in past centuries resembled almost a small Venice, crossed by waterways where the main roads are now located. Just along these waters came the marble blocks for the construction of the Duomo of Milan. The canals were filled to allow the cars to circulate, but this area has maintained its original beauty.

- Duomo di Milano: The majestic cathedral symbol of the city.
- Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II: Elegant historical shopping centre with luxury boutiques.
- Corso Buenos Aires: One of the main shopping streets, with numerous shops and cafés.

Nearby Activities and Places of Interest

- Parco Trotter: A green oasis ideal for jogging, picnics and outdoor activities, with children's play areas and sports fields.

description:
In the most elegant street in Milan, among luxury and prestigious brands boutiques of Quadrilatero della Moda, in an elegant building you find this cozy apartment, renovated with all comforts. Quiet because it faces an internal courtyard but in the heart of the city.
A comfortable bed, well-equipped kitchen, comfortable bathroom, office area, AC, WIFI, washer-dryer... make your stay truly unique.

neighborhood_overview:
Milan's fashion district is considered the world's most important luxury shopping district.

It is so called because it is bordered by four prestigious streets: Via Montenapoleone (where the apartment is located!), Via Manzoni, Via della Spiga and Corso Venezia. This area is home to many showrooms and ateliers of major Italian and international luxury designers, as well as jewelers, perfumeries, and design and furniture boutiques.

THE STREETS OF THE QUADRILATERAL

The fashion district is made up of the most elegant streets in Milan, including Via Montenapoleone, Via Borgospesso, Via Santo Spirito, Via del Gesù, Via Sant'Andrea and Via Bagutta. These streets are perfect for strolling and admiring the shop windows, which are often real compositions of taste and design.

The Fashion District is home to all the major luxury brands, such as Armani, Gucci, Versace, Alberta Ferretti, Cartier, Valentino, Dolce and Gabbana, Prada, Fendi, Louis Vuitton,
